narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I increased my knowledge of Middle Egyptian.
You mainly translate texts and go over the grammar of them in class.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Great course with an amazing and engaging professor.
This is a wonderful course. It might be nice to have some guidance as to what are the best words to memorize - 100 most important verbs, etc. But this is also something you can do on your own.
The strengh is that Professor Darnell is great and really cares and his students. The class and texts are interesting but they are a lot of work and can be frustrating at times.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you have made it through L1 and L2, it is really exciting to finally have all that hard work pay off and be able to read actual documents.
This is a good course to take, it will require work but the class is only one day a week. Not a bad language.
